      • executeQuery

        protected java.sql.ResultSet executeQuery(java.sql.Connection dbConn,
                                          java.lang.String prepStatement,
                                          java.lang.Object... args)
                                   throws java.sql.SQLException
        Passes a general query statement through the provided dbConn. Acts as a mediator between the database object and the calling method.
        Parameters:
        dbConn - An active connection to a database, presumably provided by a getConnection() implementation.
        prepStatement - A string representing the prepared statement.
        args - Arguments representing the fillers for the ?s in the prepared statement.
        Returns:
        A ResultSet representing the values returned from the database. This requires the connection to remain open, so it takes the dbConn as an argument.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - Forwards SQLExceptions to be dealt with by the other functions
